00:10:57.265 --> 00:10:59.660
>> OLE: When it comes
to designing something

00:10:59.660 --> 00:11:05.280
for public use in Denmark,
we have some laws,

00:11:05.280 --> 00:11:11.190
we have to follow these laws
are the national implementation

00:11:11.190 --> 00:11:13.070
of EU legislation.

00:11:13.070 --> 00:11:19.540
It began in 2018.

00:11:19.540 --> 00:11:24.760
It more or less says, "You have to
comply to the European standard.

00:11:24.760 --> 00:11:28.320
When it comes to accessibility,"
that means compliance

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:37.090
with EN 301549, Chapter 9,
which is about web documents.

00:11:39.050 --> 00:11:48.760
Most of this document actually just
refers to the WCAG 2.1 AA level.

00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:54.970
Compliance is actually
hard, but not impossible.

00:11:57.000 --> 00:12:01.960
What was really interesting about
compliance was that when we talked

00:12:01.960 --> 00:12:10.210
with different developers out
there with the new web design,

00:12:10.210 --> 00:12:15.950
we actually had the problem
that we knew more than them.

00:12:15.950 --> 00:12:18.020
I think that Nick
stated in the keynote,

00:12:18.020 --> 00:12:24.670
that he also had problems
finding a place where he could go

00:12:24.670 --> 00:12:30.740
to get help and actually have
them do the things right.

00:12:33.090 --> 00:12:35.210
We had the same problem.

00:12:36.240 --> 00:12:41.620
We knew we wanted compliance,
we thought we could do that.

00:12:41.620 --> 00:12:43.850
That was great.

00:12:43.850 --> 00:12:48.660
One of the few things that's
important in Denmark when it comes

00:12:48.660 --> 00:12:54.290
to EU legislation is you also have to
have a web accessibility statement.

00:12:54.290 --> 00:12:57.850
In Denmark, we have to have a
link in the footer and we have

00:12:57.850 --> 00:13:05.620
to have a smart-URL that the
site special vests, which points

00:13:05.620 --> 00:13:11.542
to the Danish web accessibility
statement repository

00:13:11.543 --> 00:13:14.000
in the public bodies.

00:13:15.620 --> 00:13:20.840
In there, we have described what is
good, what is not good, and so on.

00:13:20.840 --> 00:13:23.100
One of the other things
that actually is great

00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:27.510
about the law is there has
to be a feedback mechanism.

00:13:27.510 --> 00:13:31.080
For us, we have a phone
number, and we have an email.

00:13:31.080 --> 00:13:37.250
We really make it clear
that we don't want people

00:13:37.250 --> 00:13:40.860
sending us personal information,
because that's always a danger

00:13:40.860 --> 00:13:46.640
when it comes to sending
emails, at least for us being

00:13:46.640 --> 00:13:47.820
in the health area.

00:13:49.610 --> 00:13:53.020
When it comes to laws and standards,
it's pretty clear what we had to do.

00:13:55.730 --> 00:13:59.340
One of the things
that I was happy about

00:13:59.340 --> 00:14:05.410
when we had this problem was when
it comes to these kinds of things.

